---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const trail = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'About', href: '/about' },
];
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Colin Shove is a web designer and developer running Frively, building high-performance sites for local businesses across the UK."
  breadcrumbs={trail}
>
  <article class="measure">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I am Colin Shove, a web designer and developer based in the UK. I run
      <a href="https://frively.com">Frively</a>, where I build websites for
      local businesses to a hardcoded performance standard I call The
      Visibility Spec.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Spec exists because lots of small businesses get sold underperforming
      websites by providers who knew better but cut corners. Clients could not
      tell the difference, so corners stayed cut. I treat technical performance
      and structured site architecture as non-negotiable standards, the same way
      global brands do, and apply them on every page of every site I build.
    </p>

    <h2>What I write about here</h2>

    <p>
      This site is for the thinking that does not fit on the Frively site:
      longer essays on web performance and dev craft, commentary on the local
      web industry, tutorials when something is worth explaining properly, and
      personal essays when the topic strays off-piste.
    </p>

    <h2>Where to find me</h2>

    <p>
      The best way to reach me is via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      I read everything that comes through it. For Frively work, the
      <a href="https://frively.com">main site</a> is the front door.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
